7:["$","article",null,{"className":"min-h-screen bg-white","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12","children":[["$","header",null,{"className":"mb-8","children":[["$","h1",null,{"className":"text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4","children":"How to identify risk significance in ISO 9001"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"flex items-center gap-4 text-gray-600","children":[["$","time",null,{"dateTime":"2026-01-02T06:31:13+00:00","children":"January 2, 2026"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"inline-block px-3 py-1 bg-blue-100 text-blue-800 rounded-full text-sm","children":"general"}]]}]]}],null,["$","div",null,{"className":"mb-8 p-4 bg-gray-50 rounded-lg border-l-4 border-blue-500","children":["$","p",null,{"className":"text-gray-700 italic","children":"While implementing ISO 9001 certification, it is recommended that before planning what to do about the risks in your organizations QMS, it is quite important"}]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"prose prose-lg max-w-none mb-8 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed","children":[["$","p","0",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"How to identify risk significance in ISO 9001"}],["$","p","1",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"With the new edition of the ISO 9001 certification standard's necessities for building an impeccable Quality Management System (QMS), the new idea of risk based thinking has brought to surface with some inarticulate ways to implement this new updated ISO certification needs and requirements. Whereas some organizations were already employing a SWOT analysis (strength, weakness, opportunity, threat) on their organization to assist them to pinpoint or identify risks in all areas. However, this method of analysis is not decisive and provide sufficient data on how to address these risks once they're identified. So, how does one assess the significance of the risk once it is recognized what it is?"}],["$","p","2",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"What is significance of risk in ISO 9001 QMS?"}],["$","p","3",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"When you to know how to addresses the ISO 9001 risks and opportunities, the ISO 9001 QMS standard's necessities will need you to determine risks, plan your reaction to it, integrate it into this ISO certification system and assess its efficacy. In order to make sure the effectiveness of the implemented process or method you need from your risk response, there is one way you may need to do as a part of planning your response: Determine how significant your risk is. In other words, how vital is the risk?"}],["$","p","4",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"For people who perceive the Failure Modes and Effects Analysis (FMEA) method, you may be accustomed to the actual fact that there are many things to contemplate when deciding what risk is, its severity of incidence, chances of occurrence and chance of detection. The possibility of detection is influenced by the controls you set in your organization, that has not however been discussion to mitigate his severity and recurrence. The severity and likelihood of incidence, however, are the 2 things you may want to think about while assessing the significance of the risks."}],["$","p","5",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"It is significant to contemplate how dangerous the potential risks can be (severity), considering the fact that how likely it is that the issues or problems can happen (probability). If a risk could cause a problem that you just suppose can have radical consequences, and also the probability of the risk happening is extremely feasible, then this can be a significant risk that you just will need to do some essential actions or measures regarding this. On the contrary, if you have identified a risk which will cause a minor inconvenience, and isn't likely to happen, then perhaps this can be a risk that you simply can prefer to do nothing to forestall and just react without any complication in order to mitigate the severity and probability of recurrence."}],"$L10","$L11","$L12","$L13","$L14"]}],"$L15"]}]}]
